Package address.data

Class AddressEntry

java.lang.Object
address.data.AddressEntry
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<AddressEntry>
public class AddressEntry extends Object implements Comparable<AddressEntry>
The AddressEntry class represents a generic Address Entry used to store all the information or data for a user's address entry.
Since:
JDK 17

    • compareTo

      public int compareTo(AddressEntry other)
      Used to properly add elements in the TreeMap for the add module in AddressBook as it needs to "return" a boolean value in TreeSetadd(). This is because the original compareTo() is used for single data types while TrTreeSetadd() holds multiple data in a single object.
      Specified by:
      compareTo in interface Comparable<AddressEntry>
      Parameters:
      AddressEntry - is an AddressEntry object
      Returns:
      a boolean value of 0 and 1, it compares the data of the address entry from last name to zip code.
